															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(637830); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=637830&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251596" alt="SoullessSingularity" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=637830)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(637830); return false;" >SoullessSingularity</a></span> <span class="odate time_1535696794 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 Aug 2018 06:26</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3945375">
									

<p>Hey y'all, people have mentioned they might find this useful. I'm going to post about publishing opportunities for real life, mostly in short stories. I will be posting entirely paid publishing markets, their length requirements and pay amounts, as well as a general idea of what they're looking for. Some things to note:</p>
<p><strong>Pro-Pay:</strong> <a href="https://www.sfwa.org/">The Science Fiction and Fantasy Writers of America</a> determine that a professional rate is 6 cents a word, minimum $60.</p>
<p><strong>Semi-Pro Pay:</strong> Anywhere from 1c/word to 5c/word.</p>
<p><strong>Token:</strong> These publishing markets will pay a flat rate regardless of word count.</p>
<p><strong>Flash Fiction:</strong> Generally, these are below 1k words long.</p>
<p>As a beginning post, I'll list the markets that currently qualify as professional rate markets. It's a good idea to read each market's deadlines, guidelines, and any free stories available to get an idea if the market is looking for work you write.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.analogsf.com/">Analog Science Fiction and Fact</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.apex-magazine.com/submission-guidelines/">Apex</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.arcmanor.com/">Arc Manor</a></li>
<li><a href="https://aresmagazine.com/">Ares Magazine</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.asimovs.com/">Asimov’s Science Fiction</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.beneath-ceaseless-skies.com/">Beneath Ceaseless Skies</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.castofwonders.org/">Cast of Wonders</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.chaosium.com/fiction-submissions">Chaosium</a></li>
<li><a href="http://cicadamag.com/">Cicada</a></li>
<li><a href="http://clarkesworldmagazine.com/">Clarkesworld Magazine</a></li>
<li><a href="http://compellingsciencefiction.com/">Compelling Science Fiction</a></li>
<li><a href="https://cosmicrootsandeldritchshores.com/">Cosmic Roots and Eldritch Shores</a></li>
<li><a href="https://shop.cricketmedia.com/">Cricket</a></li>
<li><a href="https://dailysciencefiction.com/">Daily Science Fiction</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.diabolicalplots.com/">Diabolical Plots</a></li>
<li><a href="http://escapepod.org/">Escape Pod</a></li>
<li><a href="https://firesidefiction.com/">Fireside Fiction</a></li>
<li><a href="http://flashfictiononline.com/main/">Flash Fiction Online</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.faa2001.com/home/submissions-guidelines/">Future Affairs Administration</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.galaxysedge.com/">Galaxy’s Edge Magazine</a></li>
<li><a href="https://grantvillegazette.com/wp/">Grantville Gazette</a></li>
<li><a href="https://grimoakpress.com/">Grim Oak Press</a> (Known for mostly novels)</li>
<li><a href="https://www.highlights.com/">Highlights</a> (children's general lit)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.lightspeedmagazine.com/">Lightspeed Magazine</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.sfsite.com/fsf/">The Magazine of Fantasy and Science Fiction</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.mzbworks.com/">Marion Zimmer Bradley Literary Works Trust</a> (Closed to unsolicited submissions)</li>
<li>Nature (general science magazine)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.nightmare-magazine.com/">Nightmare Magazine</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.intergalacticmedicineshow.com/">Orson Scott Card’s InterGalactic Medicine Show</a></li>
<li><a href="http://podcastle.org/">PodCastle</a></li>
<li><a href="http://pseudopod.org/">PseudoPod</a></li>
<li><a href="http://strangehorizons.com/">Strange Horizons</a></li>
<li><a href="https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/topic/terraform">Terraform (Motherboard)</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.tor.com/">Tor.com</a> (Mostly Novels)</li>
<li><a href="https://uncannymagazine.com/">Uncanny Magazine</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.writersofthefuture.com/">Writers of the Future Anthology</a> Contest. There be Scientologists here! Be forewarned!</li>
<li><a href="http://www.zombiesneedbrains.com/">Zombies Need Brains</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Please see the SFWA site directly for the current and updated markets that are pro-rate.</p>
<p>I also welcome other people post what they find. And if anyone has any questions about the submission process, here is also a good place.</p>

