														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3945383">
									

<p><a href="http://compellingsciencefiction.com/guidelines.html">Compelling Science Fiction</a> is a professional rate market, previously closed to submissions. They've recently stated their submission window will be open for two months, from October 1 to December 1. Compelling Science Fiction is looking for the following:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The stories we accept almost always:<br /></p>
<ol>
<li>illustrate at least one interesting concept,</li>
<li>are engaging, and</li>
<li>clearly explain the science/technology in the story.</li>
</ol>
<p><em>We certainly won't dismiss a well-written dystopian future, but we have a bias toward stories that depict technological advancement rather than decay. We do not publish fantasy stories (although we enjoy them!). Finally, humor is always appreciated &#8212; I emphasize this because we receive so little of it.</em></p>
</blockquote>

